\description{
\code{friedman_test()} compares three or more related measurements from the
same subjects when your data isn't normally distributed. It's the non-parametric
alternative to repeated-measures ANOVA.

Think of it as:
\itemize{
\item Comparing ratings of multiple items by the same respondents
\item Testing whether scores change across three or more time points
\item A robust repeated-measures comparison that works with any data shape
}

The test tells you:
\itemize{
\item Whether at least one measurement is significantly different from the others
\item Which measurements tend to be rated higher or lower (via mean ranks)
\item The strength of the overall effect (Kendall's W)
}
